{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.6",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 6 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:1",
      "text": "My son, if thou be surety for thy friend, if thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:2",
      "text": "Thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:3",
      "text": "Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend; go, humble thyself, and make sure thy friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:4",
      "text": "Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:5",
      "text": "Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand of the hunter, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:6",
      "text": "Go to the ant, thou sluggard; consider her ways, and be wise:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:7",
      "text": "Which having no guide, overseer, or ruler,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:8",
      "text": "Provideth her meat in the summer, and gathereth her food in the harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:9",
      "text": "How long wilt thou sleep, O sluggard? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:10",
      "text": "Yet a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:11",
      "text": "So shall thy poverty come as one that travelleth, and thy want as an armed man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:12",
      "text": "A naughty person, a wicked man, walketh with a froward mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:13",
      "text": "He winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:14",
      "text": "Frowardness is in his heart, he deviseth mischief continually; he soweth discord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:15",
      "text": "Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:16",
      "text": "These six things doth the Lord hate: yea, seven are an abomination unto him:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:17",
      "text": "A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:18",
      "text": "An heart that deviseth wicked imaginations, feet that be swift in running to mischief,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:19",
      "text": "A false witness that speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:20",
      "text": "My son, keep thy father’s commandment, and forsake not the law of thy mother:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:21",
      "text": "Bind them continually upon thine heart, and tie them about thy neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:22",
      "text": "When thou goest, it shall lead thee; when thou sleepest, it shall keep thee; and when thou awakest, it shall talk with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:23",
      "text": "For the commandment is a lamp; and the law is light; and reproofs of instruction are the way of life:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:24",
      "text": "To keep thee from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:25",
      "text": "Lust not after her beauty in thine heart; neither let her take thee with her eyelids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:26",
      "text": "For by means of a whorish woman a man is brought to a piece of bread: and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:27",
      "text": "Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:28",
      "text": "Can one go upon hot coals, and his feet not be burned?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:29",
      "text": "So he that goeth in to his neighbour’s wife; whosoever toucheth her shall not be innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:30",
      "text": "Men do not despise a thief, if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:31",
      "text": "But if he be found, he shall restore sevenfold; he shall give all the substance of his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:32",
      "text": "But whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding: he that doeth it destroyeth his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:33",
      "text": "A wound and dishonour shall he get; and his reproach shall not be wiped away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:34",
      "text": "For jealousy is the rage of a man: therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.6.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 6:35",
      "text": "He will not regard any ransom; neither will he rest content, though thou givest many gifts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
